Course data for examples

Source: R/data.R
toy_course.Rd

A small subset by row and column of the MIDFIELD course table for use in package examples.

toy_course

Format

data.table with 4616 rows and 6 columns keyed by student ID.

mcid

Character, anonymized student ID.

institution

Character, de-identified institution name, e.g., Institution A, Institution B, etc.

term

Character, academic year and term, format YYYYT.

abbrev

Character, course alpha identifier, e.g. ENGR, MATH, ENGL.

number

Character, course numeric identifier, e.g. 101, 3429.

grade

Character, course grade, e.g., A+, A, A-, B+, I, NG, etc.

See also

Other toy-data: toy_degree, toy_student, toy_term
